{
  "text": "We analyzed three gene expression datasets. The first dataset was collected by Kang et al. using microarrays from the brains of 57 human donors [CITATION_1] . The dataset contained transcriptome of 17,565 mainly protein-coding genes collected from 11 cortical and 5 sub-cortical brain regions. We included all subjects older than 10 post conceptual week (PCW), leaving a total of 53 subjects aged 10PCW to 82 years. The data were originally quantile-normalized and log 2 -transformed. When presenting results, we followed the classification of subjects into 13 age groups made in [CITATION_2] and specified in Table 1 . Classification into age groups was not used in the analysis.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "55848",
    "[CITATION_2]": "55848"
